      "writtenOn": "2017-09-26T16:33:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i didn\u0027t review this proto before and you are making backward incompatible changes, so I think I\u0027d start a discussion here.\n\ni think i have two concerns with this:\n1) the schema invites the user to use this as a primary key. File system paths do not define the source. It is defined by hashes of isolate/commits/packages/etc.\n2) it might be that not everything can be represented as a file system path. Imagine that another input to the task is a config that it fetched every time, stored in memory (not file system), acted on and discarded. What should we use as they key then?\n\nI think I\u0027d rather move the concept of the file system to the types of sources that understand it instead of making this type centered around fs path. Then this message would contain\n\nrepeated GitCheckout git;\nrepeated CIPDDeployment cipd;\nrepeated IsolatedDeployment isolated;\nrepeated SomeOtherKindOfSource blah;\n\nor\n\n// key is repo URL\nrepeated map\u003cstring, GitCheckout\u003e git;\n// key is CIPD package name\nrepeated map\u003cstring, CIPDPackage\u003e cipd;\n\nand each of them may contain checkout/deployment path. Or maybe not? Does milo use the path? Does manifest hash depend on fs paths? Should it?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 124,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 124,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "bdd3005e4bd1ef2b18817e2052f9ca2c99b3c392",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
